</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1>Resounding Software </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="row-fluid menu">
            <div class="span3">
                <a class="btn btn-large btn-success" href="http://resoundingsoftware.wordpress.com">Visit our Blog</a>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <a class="btn btn-large btn-info" href="http://apps.resounding.ca">See our Apps</a>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <a class="btn btn-large btn-danger" href="http://tourney.resounding.ca">Take a Tour</a>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <a class="btn btn-large btn-warning" href="mailto:cliffe@resounding.ca">Contact Us</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row-fluid links">
            <div class="span4 devices">
                <a href="#devices">
                    <img src="../../Content/img/smartphone.png" alt="Devices" />
                    <h1>Devices</h1>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="span4 processes">
                <a href="#processes">
                    <img src="../../Content/img/gears.png" alt="Processes" />
                    <h1>Processes</h1>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="span4 performance">
                <a href="#performance">
                    <img src="../../Content/img/racecar.png" alt="Performance" />
                    <h1>Performance</h1>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section id="devices">
            <h1>Devices</h1>
            <p class="lead">Smartphones & tablets are everywhere today.</p>
            <p>Are you just coping with that fact, or are you using it to your advantage?
            We'll help you ensure that your internal and public-facing websites both look good
            and work well on mobile devices and tablets, giving you a real competitive advantage.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="processes">
            <h1>Processes</h1>
            <p class="lead">Sometimes it's the little things that hurt you.</p>
            <p>Like manual processes that eat away at your time and money, killing your productivity. Things like:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Sending out packages and documents in the courier.</li>
                <li>Approving purchases for non-production items.</li>
                <li>Matching up Work Orders with the work one (and billing for it!).</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We can help you streamline and automate these types of processes. You'll reduce
            labour, save paper and increase reportability.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="performance">
            <h1>Performance</h1>
            <p class="lead">Offline access, the Realtime Web, Social Media...</p>
            <p>The Internet moves quickly. We're up to date with the latest trends and techniques that
            will ensure your sites perform well and utilize the best that the web has to offer.</p>
        </section>
    </div>

    <script type="text/javascript">
    $(function() {

        var enter = function(img) {
            img.attr('src', img.attr('src').replace('.png', '-hover.png'));
        };

        var leave = function(img) {
            img.attr('src', img.attr('src').replace('-hover', ''));
        };

        $('.links a>img')
            .mouseenter(function() {
                enter($(this));
            })
            .mouseleave(function() {
                leave($(this));
            });

        $('.links a>h1')
            .mouseenter(function() {
                enter($(this).siblings('img'));
            })
            .mouseleave(function() {
                leave($(this).siblings('img'));
            });
    });    
    </script>
</body>
</html>
